Site Criticism Team - Review


22 Dec 2019 12:29






Since the above comments don't really offer much in addressing the piece, I'd like to offer a review.

That's not to say that I didn't enjoy it. I'm really quite moo-ved myself.

+[Critique]Access

-[ClickText]


I remember being a bit confused when you showed me this in a draft and the following conversation that occurred in IRC made it a bit clearer what was going on, but it wasn't coming clearly in the article itself. Coming back to it now, I feel that it is very clear what is going on: the cows are easily won over with special treats. The addition of references to cartoonish representations of adoration does so nicely here, giving it a pleasant feeling of  while showing off such actions in a manner that could be considered gross if you saw it in person.

I think the inclusion of the Valentine's Day cards is a bit much, personally. While it does get the point across a bit firmer, it seems like it is almost too forward. It's not an addition I would have put in myself, but I can see why you would include it. That, however, is a small detail that I can overlook. I thoroughly enjoyed the weirdness of this piece, and feel it has earned one uplike.




SoullessSingularity, for any questions or concerns relating to this review.







